Be wary of advertisements or advice that tells you to exercise less, not more, says sports medicine expert Jon Patricios. People who exercise regularly live longer lives than those who don’t. They also get sick less often and are less likely to be admitted to hospital. There’s an easy equation you can use to figure out how far you should be pushing your body. And, it only takes half an hour of exercise on weekdays to lengthen your life. This story was produced by the Bhekisisa Centre for Health Journalism. Sign up for the newsletter.